solution:
Let $a = 5 + 10i,$ $b = 7 + 2i,$ and $c = 11 + 3i.$  Let $d$ be the fourth vertex.

Note that
\[c - b = 4 + i\]and
\[a - b = -2 + 8i = 2i(4 +i) = 2i(c - b).\]Thus, the angle between the segment joining $a$ and $b$ and the segment joining $b$ and $c$ is $90^\circ.$

[asy]
unitsize(0.5 cm);

pair A, B, C, D;

A = (5,10);
B = (7,2);
C = (11,3);
D = (9,11);

draw(A--B--C--D--cycle);
draw(A--C,dashed);
draw(B--D,dashed);

dot("$a = 5 + 10i$", A, W);
dot("$b = 7 + 2i$", B, S);
dot("$c = 11 + 3i$", C, E);
dot("$d = 9 + 11i$", D, N);
dot((A + C)/2);
[/asy]

As a rectangle, the midpoints of the diagonals coincide.  The midpoint of $a$ and $c$ is
\[\frac{5 + 10i + 11 + 3i}{2} = 8 + \frac{13}{2} i,\]so
\[d = 2 \left( 8 + \frac{13}{2} i \right) - (7 + 2i) = \boxed{9 + 11i}.\]

The number of men and the amount of time to dig the foundation are inversely proportional.  Let $m$ equal the number of men and $d$ equal the number of days to complete the foundation.  This implies that $md=k$ for some constant $k$.  From the given information, $15\cdot 4=60=k$.  Knowing the value of $k$ we can solve for the number of days it would have have taken 25 men to dig the foundation: \begin{align*}
25\cdot d&=60\\
\Rightarrow\qquad d&=60/25=12/5=\boxed{2.4}
\end{align*}

